name: Cymbidium
description: Cymbidium is a genus of about 50 species in the family Orchidaceae, native to high altitudes in Southeast Asia, though several species are native to northern Australia.These plants have long stems that produce beautiful, exotic, waxy-looking flowers. They grow on rocks or tree branches in nature. They are one of the most popular orchids in the world because of their easy maintenance, adaptability and spectacular flowers in a wide range of colors.
meaning: The genus name is derived from the Greek “kymbe”, meaning “boat”, referring to the shape of the flowers lip.
color_description: Cymbidium comes in various colors such as white, green, yellow, brown, orange, pink and red.
